%I A396411 #7 Jun 01 2026 22:28:36
%S A396411 0,0,0,0,688,4034500,2051388135
%N A396411 Number of relations R on an n-element set such that the transitive closure of R has exactly ten elements more than R.
%C A396411 Equivalently, a(n) is the number of binary relations R on an n-set for which exactly ten ordered pairs must be adjoined to obtain a transitive relation; i.e., |closure(R) \ R| = 10.
%e A396411 For n <= 3 we have n^2 <= 9, so a relation differing from its closure by ten pairs would have to be empty requiring ten ordered pairs for transitive closure, which is impossible. Hence a(0) = a(1) = a(2) = a(3) = 0.
%Y A396411 Cf. A006905, A395083, A395919, A395920, A396053, A396054, A396055.
